              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>For any two sets <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>, we may form the <html:em><html:strong>empty <fr:link href="/jms-00I7/" title="Relation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I7/" display-uri="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link></html:strong></html:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varnothing \colon  A\mathbin {\nrightarrow } B]]></fr:tex> that relates <html:em>no</html:em> elements. In other words, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varnothing ]]></fr:tex> is the empty subset of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\times  B]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
