              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>For any set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, we can form the <html:em><html:strong>identity <fr:link href="/jms-00I7/" title="Relation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I7/" display-uri="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link></html:strong></html:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {id}_{A}\colon  A\mathbin {\nrightarrow } A]]></fr:tex>, also called the <html:em><html:strong>equality <fr:link href="/jms-00I7/" title="Relation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I7/" display-uri="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link></html:strong></html:em>, which relates each element of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> to itself. In other words, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {\mathsf {id}_{A}} a']]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a=a']]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <html:p>We have already seen the <fr:link href="/jms-00I9/" title="relations in program specification" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I9/" display-uri="jms-00I9" type="local">square root relation from positive reals to reals</fr:link>, which corresponds to a <html:em>total</html:em> but <html:em>many-valued</html:em> function. We can define an analogous relationship in <fr:link href="/jms-00IJ/" title="The integer square root relation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IJ/" display-uri="jms-00IJ" type="local">Example <fr:contextual-number uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IJ/" display-uri="jms-00IJ" /></fr:link> below from positive integers (naturals) to integers, which will correspond to a <html:em>partial</html:em> and many-valued function.</html:p>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>1</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>17</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IJ/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>jms-00IJ</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/jms-00IJ/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="The integer square root relation">The integer square root <fr:link href="/jms-00I7/" title="Relation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I7/" display-uri="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link></fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>The square root operation corresponds to a relation <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R_2\colon  \mathbb {N}\mathbin {\nrightarrow }\mathbb {Z}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m\mathrel {R_2} n]]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m = n^2]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
              <fr:contributor>
                <fr:link href="/marcelofiore/" title="Marcelo Fiore" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/marcelofiore/" display-uri="marcelofiore" type="local">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link>
              </fr:contributor>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
              <fr:month>1</fr:month>
              <fr:day>17</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IO/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>jms-00IO</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/jms-00IO/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Negation invariance of the square root relation">Negation invariance of the <fr:link href="/jms-00I9/" title="relations in program specification" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I9/" display-uri="jms-00I9" type="local">square root relation</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Recall the square root <fr:link href="/jms-00I7/" title="Relation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I7/" display-uri="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {sq}\colon \mathbb {R}_{\geq  0}\mathbin {\nrightarrow } \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> from <fr:link href="/jms-00I9/" title="relations in program specification" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I9/" display-uri="jms-00I9" type="local">Example <fr:contextual-number uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I9/" display-uri="jms-00I9" /></fr:link>, and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {neg} \colon \mathbb {R}\mathbin {\nrightarrow }\mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> be the <fr:link href="/jms-00I7/" title="Relation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I7/" display-uri="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left \{(x,y)\in \mathbb {R}^2\mid  x = -y\right \}\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. Then the <fr:link href="/jms-00IN/" title="Relational composite" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IN/" display-uri="jms-00IN" type="local">relational composite</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {neg}\circ \mathsf {sq}\colon  \mathbb {R}_{\geq  0}\mathbin {\nrightarrow }\mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> is equal to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {sq}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>17</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>By <fr:link href="/jms-00IM/" title="Relational extensionality" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IM/" display-uri="jms-00IM" type="local">relational extensionality</fr:link>, it suffices to check that for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  \mathbb {R}_{\geq  0}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y\in  \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\mathrel {{\mathopen {}\left (\mathsf {neg}\circ \mathsf {sq}\right )\mathclose {}}} y]]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\mathrel {\mathsf {sq}}y]]></fr:tex>. We compute:</html:p>

 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \begin {aligned}
   x\mathrel {{\mathopen {}\left (\mathsf {neg}\circ \mathsf {sq}\right )\mathclose {}}} y
   &\Longleftrightarrow 
   \exists  z\in \mathbb {R}\mathpunct {.}
   x\mathrel {\mathsf {sq}}z \land  z \mathrel {\mathsf {neg}}y
   \\
   &\Longleftrightarrow 
   \exists  z\in \mathbb {R}\mathpunct {.}
   x=z^2 \land  z =-y
   \\
   &\Longleftrightarrow 
   x={\mathopen {}\left (-y\right )\mathclose {}}^2
   \\
   &\Longleftrightarrow 
   x = y^2
   \\
   &\Longleftrightarrow 
   x\mathrel {\mathsf {sq}}y
  \end {aligned}
 ]]></fr:tex>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
